y_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying serialization structure**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I can strip the header from the first descriptor for BigInteger while allowing repeated descriptors in one stream. It seems that having multiple `classdesc` entries without handles is valid. The `ObjectOutputStream` typically uses back-references, but the deserializer seems okay with independent `classdesc`. Each fragment can strip the header. I’ll also need to serialize the integer block and figure out the `serialVersionUID`, maybe computing it in Java or Python for accuracy.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xGm7MYVWzZXLQGlWzcYyTv7j|fc_08bf97e503a0e26d0169fbe9b8193881a3816630f494e68c22", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nprint(hex(311058815616901812))\nPY"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8767, "output": 1433, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35288, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778117023344, "responseId": "resp_08bf97e503a0e26d0169fbe99fd55c81a390fdc8973a30d48d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_xGm7MYVWzZXLQGlWzcYyTv7j|fc_08bf97e503a0e26d0169fbe9b8193881a3816630f494e68c22", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0x4511a58411962b4\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778117048410}]}
